computeRhizomaticClosureTodos propagates spec hash-drift through the undirected spec-spec edge graph. For each changed spec C, walk the graph and emit TodoEdgeDrift for every transitively-reachable spec N (with no covering resolution, setting SourceSpecID to C on the todo), plus TodoCascade for every marker linked to N. The walk uses ONLY spec-spec edges; markers are reached through their linked spec after the walk completes — they are never graph nodes here. Markers directly linked to the changed source spec do NOT get cascade todos because TodoEdgeDrift on their direct edge already covers them. Resolutions are looked up in either direction (a (N, C) resolution is equivalent to a (C, N) resolution for coverage purposes).